N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 11.101 - Entry level qualifications

State Regulations
A public health engineer must possess a baccalaureate degree in engineering from a regionally accredited or New York State registered college or university or a license to practice as a professional engineer in New York State. Notes
